<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7277&amp;p=72033#p72033</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7277&amp;p=72033#p72033"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[I feel like making ca65 project templates]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7277&amp;p=72033#p72033"><![CDATA[
Just to let you know, the development version of CC65 makes it possible for the linker config file to import symbols. This should allow a pretty easy to use, multi-mapper template to be made, while using only one configuration file. I'm not completely sure how well it'd work, haven't thought it through yet, but I think it should work...<br /><br />Something like this should be possible:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">  ; - these define the ROM structure<br />  .define NUM_PRG_BANKS   4<br />  .define MAPPER   2 ; etc...<br />  ; - this include file calculates a bunch of variables like segment sizes<br />  ;   based on the symbols defined above, and exports them for<br />  ;   the linker configuration file<br />  ; - for example, if it wants to &quot;remove&quot; a segment, it can set its size<br />  ;   to 0<br />  ; - it also defines the iNES header<br />  .include &quot;std_nes.inc&quot;<br /></div><br /><br />Something like this should make it a lot easier for newcomers to get started with CA65.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=80">thefox</a> — Mon Dec 27, 2010 7:27 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
